  "prompt": "Can I get into an ivy league school with no extracurriculars at all?",
  "response": "It's extremely difficult to get into an Ivy League school without any extracurricular activities. These schools look for well-rounded students who demonstrate:\n\n1. Leadership\n2. Passion\n3. Initiative\n4. Community involvement\n5. Unique talents or achievements\n\nWhile exceptional academic performance (near-perfect GPA, top test scores) can help, most Ivy League schools expect students to be involved outside the classroom. If you have no extracurriculars, you would need:\n\n- Truly outstanding academic credentials\n- Exceptional standardized test scores\n- Remarkable personal essays\n- Strong letters of recommendation\n- Potentially unique life experiences\n\nRealistically, having some extracurricular activities significantly improves your chances of admission. Even if you're focused on academics, try to:\n- Join a club\n- Volunteer\n- Participate in academic competitions\n- Start a project\n- Show initiative in some way\n\nIf you're early in your high school career, there's still time to build a strong extracurricular profile.",
